

	Many of you are familiar with my maps of my birthland, and 
some have already approached me as to when I would complete a set
for my new home (Fayd).

	Well, here they are.  Included in this first release are
the town, the area around Fayd, the Beach along the Inner Sea, the
Grymwoods, and the Teeth of Shartan Mountain range.

	For those that are familiar with my standard releases, you'll
notice that I have not included the standard charts and list I usually
do.  Oh, yes, I've already started them, but I am far too naive to
post them for others to use.  In addition, I am beginning to believe
that the richness and depth of Legends might be spoiled by releasing
those types of lists, and I don't want to do that.

	For those of you that aren't familiar with my work, here's
the standard message;  These maps are presented to you as is, with
absolutely no guarantee that they are correct.  They are the maps I
use, and I simply present them here, to share with you.

	Please be aware, and understand, there are certain "things"
that are not intentionally on these maps.  This may be because they
aren't absolutley necessary to the game, because it is information
that once learned is just "known", and it very well may be because
I don't want to ruin the experience for you.

	Additionally, understand that I take some liberties when I
create these maps, in order to get them as compact (use a few pages
as possible) as I can.  These liberties might take the form of having
a trail appear to go Southeast when in fact it might go North, or
breaking up a contiguous "area" at a logical point (spreading across
two pages).

	My point here is, check out the areas yourself.  Don't just
take these maps and run, never stopping to smell the roses.  Alot of
time and effort (very creative effort I might add), has gone into the
room descriptions.  Don't deprive yourself of the enjoyment.

	These maps come in two formats; Amiga IFF (the format in
which they are created) and IBM GIF.  I present them to the IBMers
in a GIF format because that is the format I can most faithfully
reproduce them.  If you prefer PCX, there are tools available to
convert them with.  As for you Atari and MAC users.......well I hope
you can find a tool to convert the IFF or GIF format.  I've seen 
them, but I don't know squat about either of these machines.

	I hope you enjoy them, and I hope they are a useful addition
to your Legends arsenal.  I'll release updates as I create them and
as they become significant enough to make the download worthwhile.
If you find any glaring problems or mistakes, have any questions,
complaints, or suggestions, feel free to contact me.


					Brett
